        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <head>25. Minutes of Director of Central Intelligence <persName corresp="#p_SWB_1"
                        >Smith</persName>’s Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d25fn1">Source:
                        Central Intelligence Agency, Office of the Director of Intelligence, Job
                        80B01676R, Box 23, Folder 5, Director’s Staff Meetings. Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-09"
                        >May 9, 1951</date>.</dateline>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to Iran.]</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DAW_1">Dulles</persName> stated that in his opinion
                    only one thing could save the situation in Iran, namely to have the Shah throw
                    out <persName corresp="#p_MM_1">Mossadeq</persName>, close the Majlis and
                    temporarily rule by decree. At a later date a new premier could be installed
                    with our help. The Director asked Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DAW_1"
                        >Dulles</persName> to get in touch with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MHF_1"
                        >Matthews</persName> and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MGC_1">McGhee</persName>
                    at State Department and discuss this matter. If we are to act along these lines,
                    it may be necessary to have an <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                    directive.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
